Channel4.uk.description: In Spain, building works disrupt a B&B. A couple plan to launch two new ventures in France. And two events business owners throw a grand party in their renovated wine cellar. (S8 Ep9)

Channel4.uk.title: Car S.O.S
Channel4.uk.description: Triumph TR4: Tim Shaw and Fuzz Townshend rescue a 1962 Triumph TR4 - a British classic that turns out to be one of their biggest ever rebuilds. (S7 Ep3/10)

Channel4.uk.title: Countdown
Channel4.uk.description: Colin Murray, Rachel Riley and Susie Dent host, with Ainsley Harriott in Dictionary Corner, as contestants race against the clock to pit their wits against vowels, consonants and numbers.

Channel4.uk.title: A Place in the Sun
Channel4.uk.description: Motorbike lovers Carol and Mark dream of owning a holiday home in El Campello on the Costa Blanca. With a budget of 130k, will any of Laura Hamilton's properties get them revved up?

Channel4.uk.title: Help! We Bought a Village
Channel4.uk.description: The new series continues. In France, Kevin and Anna scale new heights to tackle tricky roof repairs. In Italy, Lucie and Jerry make a splash reinstating their borgo's old lake. (S4 Ep19/35)

Channel4.uk.title: Four in a Bed
Channel4.uk.description: The new run continues. Tensions are already bubbling away between the B&Bers before they've even arrived at Ying and Jean's inn in Powys. But the hosts have a plan to restore harmony: pies.

Channel4.uk.title: Come Dine with Me
Channel4.uk.description: North Wales. On the penultimate night, makeup artist Piers takes centre stage with a fab evening of fantastic fare. Will his guests be made up? (Ep4/5)

Channel4.uk.title: Sun, Sea and Selling Houses
Channel4.uk.description: Julie and David hope to swap wet winters in their Welsh caravan for a holiday haven on the Costa Blanca, and Tony and Sarah want to start a new life on Portugal's Algarve. (S5 Ep23)

Channel4.uk.title: Channel 4 News
Channel4.uk.description: Channel 4's flagship news programme. Including the weather.

Channel4.uk.title: The Dog House
Channel4.uk.description: A sausage dog is looking for a buddy. And a dad needs distracting when his girls are at their mum's - is pooch Papaya the answer? (S5 Ep1)

Channel4.uk.title: New: Taskmaster
Channel4.uk.description: Ania Magliano can't tell snakes and worms apart, Maisie Adam relies heavily on the lyrics to Mambo No 5, and Reece Shearsmith gets irrationally angry in a game of chance. (S20 Ep3/10)

Channel4.uk.title: New: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does...
Channel4.uk.description: ...Countdown: Jimmy Carr does the presenting as Cats Does Countdown does a compilation of comedians doing comedy while also doing the word and number games that contestants do on Countdown.

Channel4.uk.title: The Great British Bake Off
Channel4.uk.description: We're going back to school, as the bakers make canteen flapjacks, school cake and a school fete Showstopper. Who'll be top of the class, and who'll be expelled from the tent? (S16 Ep4/10) [SL]

Channel4.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
Channel4.uk.description: Zayna Flaming Grill (Part 2/2): Gordon returns to California for the conclusion of his challenge to save Zayna Flaming Grill. Can he inject flavour into the tired menu? (S7 Ep7/10) [SL]

Channel4.uk.title: Travel Man: 48 Hours in Lanzarote
Channel4.uk.description: Jessica Fostekew and Joe Lycett enjoy a Canarian caper in Lanzarote, as they trike through the lunar landscape, sample volcanic vino and cactus croquettes, and tour the lava tunnels. [SL]

Channel4.uk.title: The Inheritance
Channel4.uk.description: Devious game with Elizabeth Hurley and Robert Rinder. As whispers, betrayal and deceit ripple through the group, the Deceased challenges them to recreate her iconic fashion looks. (Ep10/12) [SL]

Channel4.uk.title: The Inheritance
Channel4.uk.description: Devious new game with Elizabeth Hurley and Robert Rinder. The Deceased unveils her most extravagant request yet: the players must take charge of her legendary Masquerade Ball. (Ep11/12) [SL]

Channel4.uk.title: The Inheritance: Final
Channel4.uk.description: As the devious game reaches its dramatic finale, The Deceased unveils a ruthless, bond-shattering, strategy-sabotaging twist. And can the ultimate Prime Beneficiary be trusted? (Ep12/12) [SL]

Channel4.uk.title: Devon and Cornwall
Channel4.uk.description: A steam engine enthusiast makes an ambitious journey across Devon in an 80-year-old steamroller. Near Falmouth, two champion free divers explore a spectacular underwater cave.

Channel4.uk.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces
Channel4.uk.description: George meets a couple risking their life savings on making a family home out of an old Airstream caravan, while his ambitious plans for a multipurpose garden building get a reality check.

Channel4.uk.title: Countdown
Channel4.uk.description: Another chance to see yesterday's new episode, with Ainsley Harriott in Dictionary Corner. Colin Murray, Rachel Riley and Susie Dent host.

Channel4.uk.title: The King of Queens
Channel4.uk.description: Road Rayge: Doug makes a new friend, Ray (guest star Ray Romano, from Everybody Loves Raymond), who has season tickets for the New York Jets. (S1 Ep9/25)

Channel4.uk.title: The King of Queens
Channel4.uk.description: Supermarket Story: Doug, Carrie and Arthur encounter chaos in the supermarket on the day before Thanksgiving. (S1 Ep10/25)

Channel4.uk.title: The King of Queens
Channel4.uk.description: Noel Cowards: Doug and Carrie can't afford the new car they want, so Arthur steps in with a distinctive gift for them. (S1 Ep11/25)

Channel4.uk.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
Channel4.uk.description: Super Bowl: Ray's sent by his paper to cover the Super Bowl, but his excitement's tempered by having to choose someone to accompany him. Will he make the right choice? (S5 Ep13)

Channel4.uk.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
Channel4.uk.description: Ray's Journal: Ray's horrified to learn that his mother used to read his diary, which contained his most personal - and perverted - thoughts. (S5 Ep14)

Channel4.uk.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
Channel4.uk.description: Silent Partners: After spending a Valentine's dinner without talking to each other, Ray and Debra agree to take an interest in each other's hobbies. (S5 Ep15)

Channel4.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4.uk.description: Daphne Hates Sherry: Daphne and Sherry just can't get on, so Daphne decides to stay at Niles's apartment. Naturally, Niles can't believe his luck. (S4 Ep21)

Channel4.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4.uk.description: Are You Being Served?: Frasier attempts to console a distraught Niles after Maris sends him their divorce papers. (S4 Ep22)

Channel4.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4.uk.description: Ask Me No Questions: When Niles asks his brother if he and Maris should stay together, Frasier is required to give his answer some careful and considered thought. (S4 Ep23)

Channel4.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4.uk.description: Odd Man Out: Frasier acts spontaneously when he realises that being single isn't all it's cracked up to be. (S4 Ep24)

Channel4.uk.title: Undercover Boss USA
Channel4.uk.description: Tim Betts, the CEO of Muscle Maker Grill, goes undercover in the restaurant chain that he recently bought. Is every branch following the same high standards? (S7 Ep4)

Channel4.uk.title: A New Life in the Sun
Channel4.uk.description: A couple host a classic car rally in France, two shop owners launch a fashion academy in Spain, and in the Charente, a couple host their first and last yoga retreat of the season. (S8 Ep10)

Channel4.uk.title: Car S.O.S
Channel4.uk.description: Toyota Celica: Tim Shaw and Fuzz Townshend travel to Northern Ireland to rescue Noel's Japanese gem - a 1972 Toyota Celica that creates a bit of a bang. (S7 Ep4/10)

Channel4.uk.title: Countdown
Channel4.uk.description: Colin Murray, Rachel Riley and Susie Dent host, with Ainsley Harriott in Dictionary Corner, as contestants race against the clock to pit their wits against vowels, consonants and numbers.

Channel4.uk.title: A Place in the Sun
Channel4.uk.description: Brian and Rita both have busy lives and can't wait to buy a holiday home on Spain's Costa Blanca for relaxing getaways with their family. Jasmine Harman shows them what their 150k can buy.

Channel4.uk.title: Help! We Bought a Village
Channel4.uk.description: The new series continues. A storm hits Kevin and Anna's French estate. Wedding bells ring at one of Carl and Francesca's villages, but a building collapses in their other one. (S4 Ep20/35)

Channel4.uk.title: Four in a Bed
Channel4.uk.description: The new run continues. It's payment day. Nowhere else will you find such consternation about whether a double bed is really a double bed if it's two single beds pushed together. Who's won?

Channel4.uk.title: Come Dine with Me
Channel4.uk.description: North Wales. Laura hosts a 'day at the races' evening. With the finish line in sight, can she gallop ahead of her rivals to take first place, or has it been a one-horse race? (Ep5/5)

Channel4.uk.title: Sun, Sea and Selling Houses
Channel4.uk.description: In Almera, Adam and Simon look for a perfect holiday home where they can embrace an al fresco lifestyle. Andrew and Katie want a place to call their own on Portugal's Algarve. (S5 Ep24)

Channel4.uk.title: Channel 4 News
Channel4.uk.description: Channel 4's flagship news programme. Including the weather.

Channel4.uk.title: New: The Great British Bake...
Channel4.uk.description: ...Off: An Extra Slice: Joel Dommett, Finlay Christie and Prue Leith mark Back to School week. Whose flapjacks got top marks? And whose Showstopper sealed their 'fete'? (S16 Ep4/10)

Channel4.uk.title: New: Gogglebox
Channel4.uk.description: The brand new series continues. What do Britain's sharpest armchair critics think of the biggest and best shows on TV this week? (S26 Ep4)

Channel4.uk.title: New: Mitchell and Webb Are Not...
Channel4.uk.description: ...Helping: The inventive and sweary new sketch show continues with a confused teacher and the search for some famous last words. Plus: an ambiguous fire drill. And who's the daddy? (Ep4)

Channel4.uk.title: American Reunion
Channel4.uk.description: (2012) Adult comedy. Jason Biggs, Alyson Hannigan and Seann William Scott star in this American Pie sequel. The class of 1999 gather to reminisce and misbehave.

Channel4.uk.title: Seven Psychopaths
Channel4.uk.description: (2012) Colin Farrell, Sam Rockwell, Christopher Walken and Woody Harrelson star in Martin McDonagh's comedy thriller about a screenwriter who gets dangerously mixed up with the Mob.

Channel4.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
Channel4.uk.description: Bella Luna: Gordon visits Italian family restaurant Bella Luna, which is struggling with an inexperienced chef and an owner who won't acknowledge the eatery's flaws. (S7 Ep8) [SL]

Channel4.uk.title: Travel Man: 48 Hours in Prague
Channel4.uk.description: Comedian Adam Buxton and Joe Lycett peruse Prague's wonders, as they kayak down the River Vltava, sample sausages out of skulls and caviar-laced ice cream, and enjoy a beer spa. [SL]

Channel4.uk.title: Location, Location, Location
Channel4.uk.description: Kirstie and Phil revisit two sets of house-hunters in East Anglia. Yvonne and Lisa left Leeds city life behind for rural Norfolk. Retirees Peggy and John wanted to be beside the seaside.

Channel4.uk.title: Kirstie and Phil's Love It or...
Channel4.uk.description: ...List It: Brilliant Builds: Kirstie and Phil look back at how Carol and Andrew balanced house and garden to create a multigenerational space in their troublesome three-bed in Harrogate.

Channel4.uk.title: The Yorkshire Dales and The...
Channel4.uk.description: ...Lakes: Season by Season: A look at the Lakes and Dales in summer, from sheep shearing in Grasmere and cricket in Cracoe to Arctic charr in Windermere. (S4 Ep3/4)

Channel4.uk.title: Cheers
Channel4.uk.description: An Old-Fashioned Wedding (Part 1/2): Kelly and Woody fight the desire to consummate their marriage before the ceremony. Carla predicts the big day will be marred by disaster. (S10 Ep25/26)

Channel4.uk.title: Cheers
Channel4.uk.description: An Old-Fashioned Wedding (Part 2/2): Woody and Kelly put on a brave face as their big day is hit by disasters involving the guests, the priest, the kitchen staff and the cake. (S10 Ep26/26)

Channel4.uk.title: Cheers
Channel4.uk.description: The Little Match Girl: Rebecca accidentally sets fire to the bar with a discarded cigarette end. Plagued by guilt, she lies to Sam, telling him that faulty wiring is to blame. (S11 Ep1/28)

Channel4.uk.title: Cheers
Channel4.uk.description: The Beer Is Always Greener: While Cheers is being redecorated, Norm, Cliff and the regulars are seduced by another bar. And is Woody and Kelly's marriage on the rocks? (S11 Ep2/28)

Channel4.uk.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
Channel4.uk.description: Fairies: Ray isn't happy about the twins' roles in the school play. (S5 Ep16)

Channel4.uk.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
Channel4.uk.description: Stefania Arrives: Robert gets a surprise visit from the gorgeous Stefania and her father. Robert fell for her in Rome, but will the holiday romance continue? (S5 Ep17)

Channel4.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4.uk.description: Frasier's Imaginary Friend: Frasier starts dating a model but their busy schedules make it difficult for them to meet, leading his family to suspect that she isn't real. (S5 Ep1)

Channel4.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4.uk.description: The Gift Horse: As Martin's 65th birthday approaches, Frasier and Niles attempt to outdo each other with their gifts. (S5 Ep2)

Channel4.uk.title: The Simpsons
Channel4.uk.description: Love Is a Many-Splintered Thing: Bart's heartstrings are pulled once again when Mary Spuckler returns to Springfield, but he doesn't pay her enough attention. (S24 Ep12/22)

Channel4.uk.title: The Simpsons
Channel4.uk.description: Boy-Scoutz 'n the Hood: During an all-syrup Squishee bender, Bart joins the junior campers, and ends up taking the embarrassing - and dangerous - Homer on a river rafting trip. (S5 Ep8/22)

Channel4.uk.title: Come Dine with Me: The...
Channel4.uk.description: ...Professionals: In Devon, there's grazing and plonk at Honky Tonk and a farm-to-fork experience at The Bear and Blacksmith. And how will Twenty Seven's fine food fare? (S2 Ep18/20)

Channel4.uk.title: A Place in the Sun
Channel4.uk.description: Andrew and Robyn love Greece and, now that they're retired, they can't wait to enjoy extended holidays on Crete. Craig Rowe shows them what their 250k can buy.

Channel4.uk.title: Four in a Bed
Channel4.uk.description: The competition begins in Perthshire, where hosts Lindsay and Pauline take their guests to a castle before finding themselves puzzled at feedback time.

Channel4.uk.title: Four in a Bed
Channel4.uk.description: The B&Bers head far north to Ross-shire, where hosts Diogo and Rafael lay on a classic Scottish offering. But there are tomato troubles and bacon bother at brekkie.

Channel4.uk.title: Four in a Bed
Channel4.uk.description: A lavatory letdown and some questionable prices cause concern at Janie and Paul's 16th-century hotel in Dumfries and Galloway.

Channel4.uk.title: Four in a Bed
Channel4.uk.description: During the week's final visit, to Morag and Jonny's glampsite in Berwickshire, the heat rises when two sets of guests fail to see eye to eye over the campfire.

Channel4.uk.title: Four in a Bed
Channel4.uk.description: After a tension-filled final visit, payment day promises to be a feisty affair. When the dust settles, who'll win the week?

Channel4.uk.title: Kirstie and Phil's Love It or...
Channel4.uk.description: ...List It: Aneri and Nihar's Radlett cottage is as cute as a button but Aneri's tired of its tight layout. Kirstie has a plan, but Phil's search leaves everyone speechless! (S10 Ep2)

Channel4.uk.title: Worst House on the Street
Channel4.uk.description: In Leicester, Stuart and Scarlette help Lianne, who's hoping to move herself and her dad out of her newly-wed brother's house and into their new home ASAP. (S3 Ep5)

Channel4.uk.title: Jamie: What to Eat This Week
Channel4.uk.description: In this cracking compilation, Jamie Oliver celebrates his fave autumnal meals, as he heroes home-grown veg and makes cheesy pasta, a smoky sweetcorn burger and tutti frutti tarte Tatin.

Channel4.uk.title: Channel 4 News
Channel4.uk.description: Channel 4's flagship news programme. Including the weather.

Channel4.uk.title: Mysteries of Sinkholes
Channel4.uk.description: From the mountains to the oceans, a deep dive into sinkholes, the terrifying phenomena that also provide a window into many of the world's unsolved archaeological mysteries. (Ep3/3)

Channel4.uk.title: Kingsman: The Secret Service
Channel4.uk.description: (2014) Action-comedy with Colin Firth, Taron Egerton and Samuel L Jackson. A London teenager is introduced to a secret society of immaculately dressed agents that exists to save the world.

Channel4.uk.title: Oasis: Supersonic
Channel4.uk.description: (2016) Acclaimed music documentary. Noel and Liam Gallagher try to remember where they were while they were getting high during Oasis's chaotic journey to superstardom in the 1990s.

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: New: The Donald Trump Show
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Donald tackles the world's biggest problems. He must make big decisions about which wars to join and on whose side. In this real-life news drama, no one knows what will happen next. (Ep3)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: New: The Shadow Scholars: Fake...
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: ...Essay Scandal: Oxford professor Patricia Kingori explores Kenya's shady, multi-billion-dollar 'fake essay' industry, where educated Kenyans write papers for students around the world.

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: New: UNTOLD: The Ibiza Final...
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: ...Boss: Haircuts & Hangovers: Documentary following Jack Kay - aka Ibiza Final Boss - as he tries to make serious money from his viral fame, with the help of an esteemed reality TV agent.

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Zayna Flaming Grill (Part 1/2): Gordon makes the first of two visits to Zayna Flaming Grill, a Mediterranean restaurant in Redondo Beach owned by Faye and her niece Brenda. (S7 Ep6/10) [SL]

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Mitchell and Webb Are Not Helping
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Mitchell and Webb's inventive and very sweary sketch show continues with a rubbish spy and ultra-competitive puritans. Plus: a dodgy sound-effects man, and the great taste of bran. (Ep3/6) [SL]

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Travel Man: 48 Hours in Trieste
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Alan Davies joins Joe Lycett for a traverse around Trieste, where they shoot the breeze at the Wind Museum and go food and fizz pairing in Prosecco. (S12 Ep1/5) [SL]

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Significant Other
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: (2022) Eerie sci-fi horror-thriller with Maika Monroe and Jake Lacy. Extra-terrestrial forces derail a couple's romantic backpacking trip, but in a subtle, non-spaceship kind of a way. [SL]

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Location, Location, Location
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Kirstie and Phil revisit architecture buffs Colin and Robin in Sussex, and sisters Gemma and Lucy in Reading, who wanted two of everything, including bathrooms and parking spaces.

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Kirstie and Phil's Love It or...
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: ...List It: Brilliant Builds - Kirstie and Phil look back on one of their most turbulent builds ever: Amber and Martin's working from home transformation in Waterbeach, Cambridgeshire.

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: George Clarke celebrates extraordinary small spaces and unique builds. This episode features a fairy-tale wooden hideaway in Bolton, and a marine-themed teardrop trailer in Kent. [SL]

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Countdown
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Another chance to see yesterday's new episode, with Ainsley Harriott in Dictionary Corner. Colin Murray, Rachel Riley and Susie Dent host.

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: The King of Queens
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Head First: Doug makes an effort to be friendlier with Arthur, and although it gets him in Carrie's good books, Doug's social standing soon takes a battering. (S1 Ep6/25)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: The King of Queens
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: The Rock: Doug and Carrie face a dilemma when she finds out that her engagement ring is a rare piece worth a lot more money than he paid for it. (S1 Ep7/25)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: The King of Queens
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Educating Doug: Carrie enrols Doug and herself on a course on Victorian novels at a local college, where Doug feels way out of his depth. But he's determined to impress Carrie. (S1 Ep8/25)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: The Sneeze: Much to Debra's annoyance, Marie mollycoddles Ray when he thinks he's coming down with something. (S5 Ep10)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Christmas Present: Ray buys Debra an elaborate Christmas present, hoping that she'll let him go on a golfing weekend. (S5 Ep11)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: What Good Are You?: Ray tries to prove his 'manliness' after failing to act swiftly enough in an emergency involving Debra. (S5 Ep12)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Roz's Turn: When a spot opens up at the radio station for a new talk show host, Roz decides that it's time for her to take the mic. (S4 Ep17)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Ham Radio: Frasier's attempt to produce a live, 1940s-style radio drama for KACL's 50th anniversary proves disastrous when Niles takes matters into his own hands. (S4 Ep18)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Three Dates and a Breakup (Part 1/2): Frasier has dates with three very different women over one weekend. Meanwhile, Martin and Sherry consider splitting up. (S4 Ep19)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Frasier
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Three Dates and a Breakup (Part 2/2): Frasier and Niles celebrate Sherry's departure with glee, but she won't give up on Martin that easily. (S4 Ep20)

Channel4Plus1.uk.title: Undercover Boss USA
Channel4Plus1.uk.description: Sam Dushey, the CEO of Shoppers World, goes incognito among his own workforce, seeking reassurance that his stores are performing to his high standards as the business grows. (S7 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Cooper Extraction: Sheldon has to go back to Texas when his sister goes into labour. While he's away, the gang gather at the flat to decorate the Christmas tree. (S7 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Hesitation Ramification: Penny's big TV acting break hits the cutting-room floor, so Leonard does his best to comfort her, which leads her to ask him a bold question. (S7 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Occupation Recalibration: Penny quits her job at the restaurant to pursue her acting career full-time. Bernadette accidentally destroys one of Howard's comics. (S7 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Convention Conundrum: After the guys miss out on Comic-Con tickets, Sheldon decides to hold his own comic book convention. The girls take tea at a swanky hotel. (S7 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Bank Job: Peralta and Diaz learn there's more to Lt Melanie Hawkins' team than meets the eye as they hunt for the gang of bank robbers. (S4 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
E4Plus1.uk.description: Crime & Punishment: Peralta and Diaz are framed for a crime they didn't commit. Can their Nine-Nine buddies save them from jail!? (S4 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Replaceable You: When Homer loses his job to his eager new assistant, he teams up with Ned to reveal her evil past. (S23 Ep4/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Ten-Per-Cent Solution: The TV network cancel Krusty the Clown's show. Can his first agent, Annie (Joan Rivers), help him craft a comeback? (S23 Ep8/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Married at First Sight UK
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: Two more singles get wed, but could a bride's pursuit of perfection jeopardise love? Plus: more honeymoon hubbub as one groom threatens the chance of romance. (S10 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Rude(ish) Tube Shorts
E4Plus1.uk.description: A short, cheeky clip from Rude Tube's naughty little sister that features a variety of cats doing strange things, some soldiers stuck in the sand and a dog balancing on a rope.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Misinterpretation Agitation: A smitten doctor turns up at Penny's door after her flirtatious sales techniques for the pharmaceutical company work a little too well. (S8 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Bart vs. Lisa vs. the Third Grade: Bart and Lisa end up in the same class when Bart's held back a year and Lisa is moved up one. (S14 Ep3/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Large Marge: Marge accidentally gets breast implants. (S14 Ep4/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Married at First Sight UK
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: MAFS UK is back, as a fresh batch of singles marry strangers! Our first couples get wed, but will an unexpected surprise and a potential ick threaten harmony? (S10 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Married at First Sight UK
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: There's a showstopping entrance and a major wobble as more strangers say 'I do'. And our first newly-weds jet off on their honeymoons, but are cracks forming? (S10 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Married at First Sight UK
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: More strangers get wed, but will a frosty first impression leave one bride out in the cold? And will there be harmonious honeymoons for our fresh newly-weds? (S10 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Married at First Sight UK
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: More singles take the leap of faith. Sparks fly for some, but one bride riles up her in-laws before she's even got down the aisle! Plus: more honeymoon hoo-ha. (S10 Ep4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Married at First Sight UK
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: Two more singles get wed, but could a bride's pursuit of perfection jeopardise love? Plus: more honeymoon hubbub as one groom threatens the chance of romance. (S10 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Below Deck
E4Plus1.uk.description: Grenadian Nightmare: Anthony buckles under pressure. A familiar face shakes up the interior. And Fraser and Barbie's drama threatens to ruin a crew day off. (S11 Ep10/17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Locomotive Manipulation: Love is in the air when Amy convinces Sheldon to join her for a romantic train trip to Napa Valley to celebrate Valentine's Day. (S7 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Indecision Amalgamation: Raj has a dating dilemma. Penny can't decide whether to accept a role in a terrible film. Sheldon chooses between two gaming systems. (S7 Ep19)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The First Pitch Insufficiency: Howard's nervous when NASA ask him to throw the first pitch at a baseball game. Sheldon claims his and Amy's relationship is the best in the gang. (S8 Ep3) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Prom Equivalency: The girls decide to re-enact their high school proms with their current partners on the roof of the apartment building. (S8 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Septum Deviation: When Leonard has to have minor surgery on his nose, Sheldon is the one who seems to need sympathy. Raj is upset when his parents split up. (S8 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Stereotypical Day: Jay goes out of his way to make a good impression on the new neighbours. (S8 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Bill's Wedding: Beverly promises to throw Bill and Dolores a perfect wedding in less than 24 hours. (S8 Ep4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Dee-Vorced: Beverly is stunned to learn that Brea's mom Vicki is divorced. Barry struggles with feeling left out of the JTP. (S8 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Eracism: After seeing Spike Lee's Do the Right Thing, Adam attempts to end racism in Jenkintown. Geoff is horrified to learn that Erica has no moral compass. (S8 Ep6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Lego Masters Australia
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - Batman: The teams create iconic vehicles for notorious Batman villains, from The Joker to Harley Quinn. Whose badass build will send them to the semi-final? (S6 Ep10/12) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Made in Chelsea: Thailand
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: Jules is livid as Molly infiltrates the group and hooks up with Tristan's bestie Chuggs. Beks kisses Freddy's best mate. And Livvy admits her eyes have wandered. (S30 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Anna Vincenzo's: Gordon Ramsay visits Italian restaurant Anna Vincenzo's in Florida, where owner CeCe has lost her way in the kitchen. But can she take constructive criticism? (S3 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Bakersfield Expedition: The guys get all dressed up for a photo opportunity at a Star Trek location but end up stranded in the desert. (S6 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
